sequenceDiagram
    participant Dev as Developer / CI
    participant APIClient as api-client<br/>Python CLI
    participant ValAPI as model-validation API<br/>HTTPS (configurable)
    participant KP as kafka-processor<br/>Python CLI
    participant Kafka as Kafka Broker<br/>9092/TCP
    participant FS as Local Filesystem<br/>data/
    participant Konflux as Konflux Build
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant InitC as Init Container<br/>(odh-model-performance-data)
    participant Volume as Shared emptyDir Volume
    participant MC as model-catalog<br/>(model-registry)

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Dev,FS: Flow 1: API-Based Data Ingestion (CI/Developer)
        Dev->>APIClient: Run data ingestion
        APIClient->>ValAPI: GET /api/v1/providers<br/>GET /api/v1/models<br/>GET /api/v1/evaluations<br/>GET /api/v1/performances<br/>GET /api/v1/validations<br/>GET /api/v1/variant-groups
        ValAPI-->>APIClient: JSON responses (paginated)
        Note over APIClient: PostProcess transforms:<br/>OverallAccuracyTransform<br/>HardwareConfigurationTransform
        APIClient->>FS: Write JSON/NDJSON files<br/>(organized by provider/model)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over Dev,FS: Flow 2: Kafka-Based Data Ingestion (CI/Developer)
        Dev->>KP: Run kafka processor
        Kafka->>KP: CDC Events<br/>(modern or Debezium format)<br/>SSL/TLS + SASL (optional)
        Note over KP: Entity detection cascade:<br/>1. Topic name mapping<br/>2. Explicit entity_type field<br/>3. Heuristic field detection
        KP->>FS: Write JSON/NDJSON files<br/>(same structure as api-client)
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over FS,Registry: Build Phase
        Konflux->>FS: COPY data/ into UBI 9 image
        Konflux->>Registry: Push container image<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Registry auth
    end

    rect rgb(248, 240, 255)
        Note over InitC,MC: Flow 3: Runtime Data Delivery (Production)
        MC->>Registry: Pull init container image<br/>HTTPS/5000 TLS
        InitC->>Volume: Copy benchmark data<br/>to emptyDir volume<br/>(File I/O)
        Note over InitC: Init container exits<br/>after copy completes
        MC->>Volume: Read benchmark data<br/>at startup (File I/O)
        Note over MC: model-catalog serves<br/>benchmark data to users
    end
